CAPE TOWN - President Jacob Zuma says social development minister Bathabile Dlamini is going nowhere. He was responding to the question on why he's not reshuffling her following the social grants payments debacle. READ: Post Office may not qualify to distribute social security grants "The Constitutional Court gave an order to that Minister. It did not give an order to any other person. That Minister that Minister has to do that order. Now if you remove her who is going to implement  that order? Who? She has to deliver on the order of  the Constitutional Court. What will i say to the constitutional court? They say this minister must deliver  and i shift this minister? What is that? She has to deliver on the order of the Constitutional Court. That's why she is there to do so!" eNCA